value.0: Congratulations, you found the doomscribe.    This obviously older woman is sitting at a desk with pages of papers already starting to pile up as she records the deaths of those who have fallen in the area that is now under her jurisdiction. You see no hair poking from beneath her head covering because like others who are doomscribes, she has shaved her head. Like others of her order, she wears robes of gray, and she chooses to make them fashionable by layering colors of gray. With her obvious age, you wonder how long it will be before Jergal comes to mummify her so she can continue her duties.  Her skeleton servants are sanctioned undead, and assist her with the ordering of the scrolls on the shelves that fill the room.

Value.value: This is a solemn undertaking. *a wry smile*
We will be under way soon. *gestures toward a tunnel entrance*
You don't like my sense of humor?  I have been told it will be the death of me.
I liked this job better when we were shoveling dirt.
Would you like a turn at breaking rock?
This will make me old before my time.

value.0: A shovel is ideal for moving quantities of dirt from one location to another.  Other uses are possible, of course.

Value.value: I hear someone is going to make the statue or whatever that will go in here. SOOOO glad it isn't me!!
My mother said an education would be better than grubbing out like this, and it is days like this that I agree with her.
